
[1]gradual

   GRAD'UAL,a. Proceeding by steps or degrees; advancing step by step;
   passing from one step to another; regular and slow; as a gradual
   increase of knowledge; a gradual increase of light in the morning is
   favorable to the eyes.

   1. Proceeding by degrees in a descending line or progress; as a gradual
   decline.
